ion, temperature, and condition summary\n- Optionally display small supporting metrics such as humidity and wind\n\n**Boundaries**\n- Focused only on the widget card\n- No unrelated interface sections should be added\n\n### 3. Static Weather Data Module\n**Responsibilities**\n- Define the static local weather payload used by the widget\n- Keep values deterministic and local to the file\n\n**Boundaries**\n- No API or network calls\n- No dynamic fetching or async flows\n\n### 4. Data Rendering Module\n**Responsibilities**\n- Map static weather data into DOM elements\n- Keep displayed values synchronized with the defined local payload\n\n**Boundaries**\n- Simple front-end assignment only\n- No extra state management required\n\n### 5. Accessibility / Readability Module\n**Responsibilities**\n- Keep contrast high enough for dark mode\n- Maintain readable structure and typography\n- Ensure semantic structure remains understandable\n\n**Boundaries**\n- Lightweight accessibility support only\n- No advanced widget controls required\n\n## File-Level Implementation Map\n\n### Recommended implementation structure\n- `weather-widget.html`\n  - semantic HTML structure\n  - embedded CSS for dark-mode glassmorphism styling\n  - embedded JavaScript for static weather data binding\n\n### Internal file map\n\n#### HTML Section\n- root preview wrapper\n- weather widget card\n- location heading/label\n- temperature display\n- condition text\n- optional supporting metrics row/grid\n\n#### CSS Section\n- dark gradient page background\n- glassmorphism card styling\n- typography hierarchy\n- metric chip styling\n- spacing and responsive rules\n\n#### JavaScript Section\n- static weather data object/constants\n- DOM references\n- render helper for assigning values into the card\n\n## Interface / API Contracts\n\n### DOM Contract\nExpected elements:\n- `.widget` as the primary card wrapper\n- `#location` for location text\n- `#temperature` for primary temperature text\n- `#condition` for condition summary\n- optional `#humidity` and `#wind` for supporting metrics\n\n### Data Contract\nStatic weather payload should contain:\n- `location: string`\n- `temperature: number | string`\n- `condition: string`\n- optional `humidity: string`\n- optional `wind: string`\n\n### Rendering Contract\n- Temperature must be the most visually prominent element\n- Text must remain legible in dark mode\n- The widget must remain self-contained and previewable without external services\n\n## Risks and Edge Cases\n\n### Visual Risks\n- glassmorphism card becoming too transparent for readability\n- muted text losing contrast against the dark background\n- oversized temperature text breaking the layout on smaller screens\n\n### Responsiveness Risks\n- narrow screens causing cramped metric layout\n- padding becoming too heavy on mobile devices\n- condition text wrapping awkwardly\n\n### Implementation Risks\n- static data not being applied to DOM correctly\n- formatting inconsistencies in displayed temperature\n- unnecessary complexity for what should be a simple widget\n\n### Accessibility Risks\n- insufficient semantic structure\n- decorative icon overpowering primary content\n- low-contrast secondary labels\n\n## Recommended Notes for Implementation\n- Keep the widget in a single file.\n- Use a simple local object for weather data.\n- Favor strong typography for temperature and subdued secondary text for metadata.\n- Maintain clean spacing so the card feels premium without becoming crowded.\nEOF\n\n$ cat > /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/TASK_BREAKDOWN.md <<'EOF'\n# Task Breakdown — PAP-30 Dark-Mode Weather Widget\n\n## Task 1 — Create the standalone widget artifact\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\n\n### Work\n- Create the standalone weather widget file.\n- Add a centered preview area and single weather card.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- File exists in the working directory.\n- Widget renders independently in a browser.\n- Card structure is clear and organized.\n\n## Task 2 — Implement dark-mode glassmorphism styling\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\n\n### Work\n- Add a dark gradient page background.\n- Style the card with glassmorphism treatment.\n- Add clean spacing, rounded corners, and polished shadows.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Card clearly reads as a modern glassmorphism surface.\n- Dark-mode presentation feels intentional and clean.\n- Text remains readable against all surfaces.\n\n## Task 3 — Add static weather content\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\n\n### Work\n- Display a local location label.\n- Display a static temperature value.\n- Display a condition summary.\n- Optionally show humidity and wind.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Temperature is visually dominant.\n- Content is readable at a glance.\n- Supporting metrics do not overpower the main data.\n\n## Task 4 — Bind static data through lightweight JS\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\n\n### Work\n- Define a local static weather data object.\n- Bind the data into the card via DOM assignments.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Displayed content matches the static object values.\n- No external API or async dependency exists.\n- JS remains simple and deterministic.\n\n## Task 5 — Final polish and responsiveness\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\n\n### Work\n- Refine typography and spacing.\n- Confirm stability on smaller screens.\n- Remove obvious visual rough edges.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Widget remains polished on desktop and mobile.\n- Layout does not break at narrow widths.\n- Final result looks review-ready.\nEOF\n\n$ cat > /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/IMPLEMENTATION_CHECKLIST.md <<'EOF'\n# Implementation Checklist — PAP-30 Dark-Mode Weather Widget\n\n## Planning\n- [x] Architecture plan created\n- [x] Task breakdown created\n- [x] Implementation checklist created\n\n## Structure\n- [ ] Create standalone weather widget file\n- [ ] Add widget card container\n- [ ] Add location element\n- [ ] Add temperature element\n- [ ] Add condition element\n\n## Styling\n- [ ] Add dark background surface\n- [ ] Add glassmorphism card styling\n- [ ] Add clear typography hierarchy\n- [ ] Add readable supporting metric styling\n- [ ] Add responsive spacing rules\n\n## Logic\n- [ ] Define static weather payload\n- [ ] Bind payload values into DOM\n- [ ] Ensure no network dependency exists\n\n## QA Readiness\n- [ ] Temperature is visually prominent\n- [ ] Dark-mode contrast is readable\n- [ ] Small-screen layout remains stable\n- [ ] Final card presentation looks polished\nEOF\n\nARCHITECT_HANDOFF_READY\n```\n\n>>> Reassigning Ticket PAP-30 to The Grunt ...\n```plaintext\n$ cat /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/ARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md\n$ cat /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/TASK_BREAKDOWN.md\n\n$ cat > /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/weather-widget.html <<'EOF'\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang="en">\n<head>\n  <meta charset="UTF-8" />\n  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />\n  <title>Dark-Mode Weather Widget</title>\n  <style>\n    :root {\n      --bg-start: #0f172a;\n      --bg-end: #1d4ed8;\n      --surface: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);\n      --surface-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14);\n      --text-main: #f8fafc;\n      --text-muted: #cbd5e1;\n      --accent: #7dd3fc;\n      --metric-bg: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.52);\n    }\n\n    * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n\n    body {\n      margin: 0;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n      display: grid;\n      place-items: center;\n      padding: 24px;\n      font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif;\n      color: var(--text-main);\n      background:\n        radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(255,255,255,0.08), transparent 30%),\n        linear-gradient(135deg, var(--bg-start), var(--bg-end));\n    }\n\n    .widget {\n      width: min(100%, 360px);\n      padding: 24px;\n      border-radius: 28px;\n      background: var(--surface);\n      border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);\n      backdrop-filter: blur(18px);\n      box-shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);\n    }\n\n    .top {\n      display: flex;\n      justify-content: space-between;\n      align-items: center;\n      gap: 16px;\n      margin-bottom: 20px;\n    }\n\n    .eyebrow {\n      margin: 0 0 6px;\n      font-size: 0.8rem;\n      color: var(--text-muted);\n      letter-spacing: 0.08em;\n      text-transform: uppercase;\n    }\n\n    #location {\n      margin: 0;\n      font-size: 1.3rem;\n      font-weight: 700;\n    }\n\n    .icon {\n      width: 60px;\n      height: 60px;\n      display: grid;\n      place-items: center;\n      border-radius: 18px;\n      background: rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.16);\n      color: var(--accent);\n      font-size: 1.75rem;\n      flex-shrink: 0;\n    }\n\n    #temperature {\n      margin: 0;\n      font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4rem);\n      line-height: 1;\n      font-weight: 800;\n    }\n\n    #condition {\n      margin: 10px 0 0;\n      color: var(--text-muted);\n      line-height: 1.5;\n    }\n\n    .metrics {\n      margin-top: 20px;\n      display: grid;\n      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);\n      gap: 12px;\n    }\n\n    .metric {\n      padding: 14px;\n      border-radius: 18px;\n      background: var(--metric-bg);\n      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);\n    }\n\n    .metric span {\n      display: block;\n      font-size: 0.8rem;\n      color: #94a3b8;\n      margin-bottom: 4px;\n    }\n\n    @media (max-width: 420px) {\n      body {\n        padding: 16px;\n      }\n\n      .widget {\n        padding: 20px;\n      }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <main class="widget" aria-label="Weather widget">\n    <div class="top">\n      <div>\n        <p class="eyebrow">Local Weather</p>\n        <h1 id="location">--</h1>\n      </div>\n      <div class="icon" aria-hidden="true">☁️</div>\n    </div>\n\n    <p id="temperature">--</p>\n    <p id="condition">Loading static conditions...</p>\n\n    <div class="metrics">\n      <div class="metric"><span>Humidity</span><strong id="humidity">--</strong></div>\n      <div class="metric"><span>Wind</span><strong id="wind">--</strong></div>\n    </div>\n  </main>\n\n  <script>\n    const weatherData = {\n      location: 'San Francisco',\n      temperature: 68,\n      condition: 'Partly cloudy · Cool evening breeze',\n      humidity: '56%',\n      wind: '8 mph',\n    };\n\n    function renderWeather(data) {\n      document.getElementById('location').textContent = data.location;\n      document.getElementById('temperature').textContent = `${data.temperature}°F`;\n      document.getElementById('condition').textContent = data.condition;\n      document.getElementById('humidity').textContent = data.humidity;\n      document.getElementById('wind').textContent = data.wind;\n    }\n\n    renderWeather(weatherData);\n\n    window.WeatherWidget = {\n      weatherData,\n      renderWeather,\n    };\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\nEOF\n\n$ cat > /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/weather-widget.test.js <<'EOF'\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst vm = require('vm');\nconst assert = require('assert');\n\nconst html = fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, 'weather-widget.html'), 'utf8');\nconst scriptMatch = html.match(/<script>([\\s\\S]*)<\\/script>/);\n\nif (!scriptMatch) {\n  throw new Error('No inline script found in weather-widget.html');\n}\n\nfunction createElement() {\n  return { textContent: '' };\n}\n\nconst elements = {\n  location: createElement(),\n  temperature: createElement(),\n  condition: createElement(),\n  humidity: createElement(),\n  wind: createElement(),\n};\n\nconst context = {\n  window: {},\n  document: {\n    getElementById(id) {\n      return elements[id];\n    },\n  },\n  console,\n};\n\ncontext.window = context;\nvm.createContext(context);\nvm.runInContext(scriptMatch[1], context);\n\nassert.ok(context.WeatherWidget, 'WeatherWidget API should be exposed');\nassert.strictEqual(context.WeatherWidget.weatherData.location, 'San Francisco');\nassert.strictEqual(context.WeatherWidget.weatherData.temperature, 68);\nassert.ok(context.WeatherWidget.weatherData.condition.includes('Partly cloudy'));\nassert.strictEqual(elements.location.textContent, 'San Francisco');\nassert.strictEqual(elements.temperature.textContent, '68°F');\nassert.ok(elements.condition.textContent.includes('Partly cloudy'));\nassert.strictEqual(elements.humidity.textContent, '56%');\nassert.strictEqual(elements.wind.textContent, '8 mph');\nassert.ok(/class="widget"/.test(html), 'widget container should exist');\nassert.ok(/backdrop-filter:\\s*blur\\(/.test(html), 'glassmorphism blur should exist');\nassert.ok(/linear-gradient\\(135deg, var\\(--bg-start\\), var\\(--bg-end\\)\\)/.test(html), 'dark background gradient should exist');\n\nconsole.log('Weather widget tests passed');\nEOF\n\n$ node /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/weather-widget.test.js\nWeather widget tests passed\n\nGRUNT_IMPLEMENTATION_DONE\n```\nUPDATE 1\n\n>>> Reassigning Ticket PAP-30 to The Pedant ...\n```plaintext\n$ sed -n '1,240p' /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/weather-widget.html\n$ node /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/weather-widget.test.js\nWeather widget tests passed\n\n$ qa_review: glassmorphism card styling confirmed\n$ qa_review: static temperature rendering confirmed\n$ qa_review: local data binding confirmed\n$ qa_review: dark-mode contrast and responsive rule present\n$ qa_review: no blocking defects found\n\nPEDANT_QA_DONE\n```\n\n>>> Reassigning Ticket PAP-30 to The Scribe ...\nI’m releasing onto the existing `feature-weather-widget` branch and restoring unrelated tracked files first so the PR only carries the intended PAP-30 changes.\n```plaintext\n$ git status --short --branch\n## feature-weather-widget...origin/feature-weather-widget\n M ARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md\n M IMPLEMENTATION_CHECKLIST.md\n D README.md\n M TASK_BREAKDOWN.md\n D calculator.html\n M weather-widget.test.js\n\n$ git restore README.md calculator.html\n\n$ git status --short\n M ARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md\n M IMPLEMENTATION_CHECKLIST.md\n M TASK_BREAKDOWN.md\n M weather-widget.test.js\n\n$ node weather-widget.test.js\nWeather widget tests passed\n\n$ git add ARCHITECTURE_PLAN.md 