ed sections, navigation, or app shell\\n\\n### 4. Static Data Module\\n**Responsibilities**\\n- Define a local static weather payload\\n- Keep the widget deterministic and self-contained\\n\\n**Boundaries**\\n- No network requests\\n- No third-party weather APIs\\n- No asynchronous fetching\\n\\n### 5. Data Rendering Module\\n**Responsibilities**\\n- Bind static weather values into the DOM\\n- Keep the rendered content aligned with the local payload\\n\\n**Boundaries**\\n- Lightweight front-end assignment only\\n- No advanced state management\\n\\n### 6. Accessibility / Readability Module\\n**Responsibilities**\\n- Maintain readable contrast in dark mode\\n- Preserve semantic structure\\n- Keep text hierarchy understandable at a glance\\n\\n**Boundaries**\\n- No complex accessibility system required\\n- Must remain simple and local to the artifact\\n\\n## File-Level Implementation Map\\n\\n### Recommended implementation structure\\n- `weather-widget.html`\\n  - semantic HTML structure\\n  - embedded CSS for dark-mode glassmorphism styling\\n  - embedded JavaScript for static weather data binding\\n\\n### Internal file map\\n\\n#### HTML Section\\n- main preview wrapper\\n- card container\\n- location text\\n- temperature display\\n- condition summary\\n- optional supporting metric items\\n\\n#### CSS Section\\n- dark gradient background\\n- glassmorphism card appearance\\n- typography hierarchy\\n- icon/accent treatment if used\\n- responsive rules for narrow screens\\n\\n#### JavaScript Section\\n- static weather object/constants\\n- DOM references\\n- render helper to assign values into the card\\n\\n## Interface / API Contracts\\n\\n### DOM Contract\\nExpected elements:\\n- `.widget` as the primary card wrapper\\n- `#location` for location text\\n- `#temperature` for primary temperature output\\n- `#condition` for condition summary\\n- optional `#humidity` and `#wind` for supporting metrics\\n\\n### Data Contract\\nStatic payload fields should include:\\n- `location: string`\\n- `temperature: number | string`\\n- `condition: string`\\n- optional `humidity: string`\\n- optional `wind: string`\\n\\n### Rendering Contract\\n- Temperature must be the visual focal point\\n- Dark-mode readability must remain strong\\n- The widget must work standalone without external services\\n\\n## Risks and Edge Cases\\n\\n### Repository / Delivery Risks\\n- Later implementation may target the wrong remote if repo state is not verified first\\n- Existing branch state may contain unrelated changes and should be isolated during implementation\\n\\n### Visual Risks\\n- Glassmorphism transparency reducing legibility\\n- Muted text losing contrast on dark gradients\\n- Temperature text overflowing on small screens\\n\\n### Responsiveness Risks\\n- Metric blocks becoming cramped on narrow widths\\n- Excess padding reducing usable space on mobile\\n- Long condition strings wrapping poorly\\n\\n### Implementation Risks\\n- Static values not being rendered into the DOM correctly\\n- Inconsistent temperature formatting\\n- Overengineering a simple static widget\\n\\n### Accessibility Risks\\n- Decorative icon drawing too much attention\\n- Weak semantic structure\\n- Low-contrast secondary labels\\n\\n## Recommended Notes for Implementation\\n- Keep the widget in a single file.\\n- Use a simple local data object and direct DOM assignment.\\n- Prioritize clear temperature hierarchy and clean spacing.\\n- During later release steps, verify the exact repository and branch before committing or pushing.\\nEOF\\n\\n$ cat > /tmp/zero-human-sandbox/TASK_BREAKDOWN.md <<'EOF'\\n# Task Breakdown — PAP-31 Dark-Mode Weather Widget\\n\\n## Task 1 — Verify working context before coding\\n**Assigned to:** Grunt\\n\\n### Work\\n- Confirm the working tree context is suitable for the requested widget work.\\n- Implement only the widget artifact and its lightweight local tests.\\n\\n### Acceptance Criteria\\n- Widget work is isolated to the requested artifact scope.\\n- No